attributes.description: This PostgreSQL dashboard shows the most important database related metrics.

params.markdown:
### PostgreSQL OpenTelemetry Metrics

This dashboard provides an overview of PostgreSQL databases through a visual representation of the data collected by [PostgreSQL OpenTelemetry Receiver](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-collector-contrib/tree/main/receiver/postgresqlreceiver). It includes:
- Query performance (execution time)
- Cache performance (shared and local)
- Transaction rates (commits and rollbacks)
- Database operations (rows returned, inserted, deleted and written)

query.query: not postgresql.statement.query.text : ("BEGIN;" or "begin" or "commit" or "end" or "END;" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_statements" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_database" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_bgwriter" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_activity")

not attributes.db.query.text : ("BEGIN;" or "begin" or "commit" or "end" or "END;" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_statements" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_database" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_bgwriter" or "SELECT * FROM pg_stat_activity")
